==Russian==

===Etymology===
German [[Hauptwache]].

===Noun===
'''гауптвахта''' (gauptváχta) {{f}}

#(''[[military|mil.]]'') a [[stockade]] (''prison'')
#(''[[military|mil.]]'') [[detention]] in a [[stockade]] as a [[punishment]]
#:{{RUchar|[[сажать|сажа́ть]] ''or'' [[отправлять|отправля́ть]] [[на]] гауптва́хту}}&nbsp;— ''to [[confine]] to [[stockade]]''
#(''[[military|mil.]], [[obsolete|obs.]]'') a [[guardhouse]] with an area for [[line-up]] of [[guard]]s
#(''[[military|mil.]], [[obsolete|obs.]]'') a [[chief]] [[guard]] of a [[city]] or a [[garrison]]

